156 void QtDcmMoveScu::run()
157 {
158  OFCondition cond;
159  step = ( int ) ( 100.0 / d->series.size() );
160  progressTotal = 0;
161 
162  for ( int i = 0; i < d->series.size(); i++ )
163  {
164  d->currentSerie = d->series.at ( i );
165  QDir serieDir ( d->outputDir + QDir::separator() + d->series.at ( i ) );
166 
167  if ( !serieDir.exists() )
168  QDir ( d->outputDir ).mkdir ( d->series.at ( i ) );
169 
170  outputDirectory = QString ( d->outputDir + QDir::separator() + d->currentSerie ).toUtf8().constData();
171 
172  if ( d->mode == IMPORT )
173  {
174  cond = this->move ( d->series.at ( i ) );
175  emit serieMoved ( serieDir.absolutePath(), d->series.at ( i ), i );
176  emit updateProgress ( ( int ) ( 100.0 * ( i+1 ) / d->series.size() ) );
177  progressTotal += step;
178  }
179  else
180  {
181  cond = this->move ( d->imageId );
182  }
183  }
184 
185  exit();
186 }

188 OFCondition QtDcmMoveScu::move ( QString uid )
189 {
190  OFString temp_str;
191  params = NULL;
192  assoc = NULL;
193  net = NULL;
194 
195  QuerySyntax querySyntax[3] =
196  {
197  { UID_FINDPatientRootQueryRetrieveInformationModel,
198  UID_MOVEPatientRootQueryRetrieveInformationModel },
199  { UID_FINDStudyRootQueryRetrieveInformationModel,
200  UID_MOVEStudyRootQueryRetrieveInformationModel },
201  { UID_RETIRED_FINDPatientStudyOnlyQueryRetrieveInformationModel,
202  UID_RETIRED_MOVEPatientStudyOnlyQueryRetrieveInformationModel }
203  };
204 
205  OFCondition cond;
206 
207  if ( d->mode == IMPORT )
208  {
209  this->addOverrideKey ( QString ( "QueryRetrieveLevel=" ) + QString ( "" "SERIES" "" ) );
210  this->addOverrideKey ( QString ( "SeriesInstanceUID=" + uid ) );
211  }
212  else
213  {
214  this->addOverrideKey ( QString ( "QueryRetrieveLevel=" ) + QString ( "" "IMAGE" "" ) );
215  this->addOverrideKey ( QString ( "SOPInstanceUID=" + uid ) );
216  }
217 
218  cond = ASC_initializeNetwork ( NET_ACCEPTORREQUESTOR, QtDcmPreferences::instance()->getPort().toInt(), acseTimeout, &net );
219 
220  if ( cond.bad() )
221  {
222  qDebug() << "Cannot create network: " << DimseCondition::dump ( temp_str, cond ).c_str();
223  return cond;
224  }
225 
226  cond = ASC_createAssociationParameters ( &params, maxPDU );
227 
228  if ( cond.bad() )
229  {
230  qDebug() << "Cannot create association: " << DimseCondition::dump ( temp_str, cond ).c_str();
231  return cond;
232  }
233 
234  ASC_setAPTitles ( params, QtDcmPreferences::instance()->getAetitle().toUtf8().data(), QtDcmManager::instance()->getCurrentPacs()->getAetitle().toUtf8().data(), QtDcmManager::instance()->getCurrentPacs()->getAetitle().toUtf8().data() );
235 
236  ASC_setPresentationAddresses ( params, QtDcmPreferences::instance()->getHostname().toUtf8().data(), QString ( QtDcmManager::instance()->getCurrentPacs()->getHostname() + ":"
237  + QtDcmManager::instance()->getCurrentPacs()->getPort() ).toUtf8().data() );
238 
239  cond = addPresentationContext ( params, 1, querySyntax[queryModel].findSyntax, networkTransferSyntax );
240  cond = addPresentationContext ( params, 3, querySyntax[queryModel].moveSyntax, networkTransferSyntax );
241 
242  if ( cond.bad() )
243  {
244  qDebug() << "Wrong presentation context:" << DimseCondition::dump ( temp_str, cond ).c_str();
245  return cond;
246  }
247 
248  cond = ASC_requestAssociation ( net, params, &assoc );
249 
250  if ( cond.bad() )
251  {
252  if ( cond == DUL_ASSOCIATIONREJECTED )
253  {
254  T_ASC_RejectParameters rej;
255  ASC_getRejectParameters ( params, &rej );
256  ASC_printRejectParameters ( temp_str, &rej );
257  qDebug() << "Association Rejected:" << QString ( temp_str.c_str() );
258  return cond;
259  }
260  else
261  {
262  qDebug() << "Association Request Failed:" << DimseCondition::dump ( temp_str,cond ).c_str();
263  return cond;
264  }
265  }
266 
267  if ( ASC_countAcceptedPresentationContexts ( params ) == 0 )
268  {
269  qDebug() << "No Acceptable Presentation Contexts";
270  return cond;
271  }
272 
273  cond = EC_Normal;
274 
275  cond = this->cmove ( assoc, NULL );
276 
277  overrideKeys->clear();
278  this->addOverrideKey ( QString ( "QueryRetrieveLevel=" ) + QString ( "" "STUDY" "" ) );
279 
280  if ( cond == EC_Normal )
281  {
282  if ( abortAssociation )
283  {
284  qDebug() << "Aborting Association";
285  cond = ASC_abortAssociation ( assoc );
286  ASC_dropNetwork ( &net );
287 
288  if ( cond.bad() )
289  {
290  qDebug() << "Association Abort Failed: " << DimseCondition::dump ( temp_str,cond ).c_str();
291  return cond;
292  }
293  }
294  else
295  {
296  /* release association */
297  qDebug() << "Releasing Association";
298 // cond = ASC_releaseAssociation(assoc); //Problem with error message Illegal Key
299  ASC_dropNetwork ( &net );
300 
301  if ( cond.bad() )
302  {
303  qDebug() << "Association Release Failed:" << DimseCondition::dump ( temp_str,cond ).c_str();
304  return cond;
305  }
306  }
307  }
308  else if ( cond == DUL_PEERREQUESTEDRELEASE )
309  {
310  qDebug() << "Protocol Error: Peer requested release (Aborting)";
311  cond = ASC_abortAssociation ( assoc );
312  ASC_dropNetwork ( &net );
313 
314  if ( cond.bad() )
315  {
316  qDebug() << "Association Abort Failed: " << DimseCondition::dump ( temp_str,cond ).c_str();
317  return cond;
318  }
319 
320  return cond;
321  }
322  else if ( cond == DUL_PEERABORTEDASSOCIATION )
323  {
324  qDebug() << "Peer Aborted Association";
325  return cond;
326  }
327  else
328  {
329  qDebug() << "Move SCU Failed: Aborting Association";
330  cond = ASC_abortAssociation ( assoc );
331  ASC_dropNetwork ( &net );
332 
333  if ( cond.bad() )
334  {
335  qDebug() << "Association Abort Failed: " << DimseCondition::dump ( temp_str,cond ).c_str();
336  return cond;
337  }
338 
339  return cond;
340  }
341 
342  return cond;
343 }

345 void QtDcmMoveScu::addOverrideKey ( QString key )
346 {
347  char * s = key.toUtf8().data();
348  unsigned int g = 0xffff;
349  unsigned int e = 0xffff;
350  int n = 0;
351  OFString dicName, valStr;
352  OFString msg;
353  char msg2[200];
354 
355  // try to parse group and element number
356  n = sscanf ( s, "%x,%x=", &g, &e );
357  OFString toParse = s;
358  size_t eqPos = toParse.find ( '=' );
359 
360  if ( n < 2 ) // if at least no tag could be parsed
361  {
362  // if value is given, extract it (and extrect dictname)
363  if ( eqPos != OFString_npos )
364  {
365  dicName = toParse.substr ( 0, eqPos ).c_str();
366  valStr = toParse.substr ( eqPos + 1, toParse.length() );
367  }
368  else
369  // no value given, just dictionary name
370  dicName = s; // only dictionary name given (without value)
371 
372  // try to lookup in dictionary
373  DcmTagKey key ( 0xffff, 0xffff );
374 
375  const DcmDataDictionary& globalDataDict = dcmDataDict.rdlock();
376 
377  const DcmDictEntry *dicent = globalDataDict.findEntry ( dicName.c_str() );
378 
379  dcmDataDict.unlock();
380 
381  if ( dicent != NULL )
382  {
383  // found dictionary name, copy group and element number
384  key = dicent->getKey();
385  g = key.getGroup();
386  e = key.getElement();
387  }
388  else
389  {
390  // not found in dictionary
391  msg = "bad key format or dictionary name not found in dictionary: ";
392  msg += dicName;
393  qDebug() << QString ( msg.c_str() );
394  }
395  } // tag could be parsed, copy value if it exists
396  else
397  {
398  if ( eqPos != OFString_npos )
399  valStr = toParse.substr ( eqPos + 1, toParse.length() );
400  }
401 
402  DcmTag tag ( g, e );
403 
404  if ( tag.error() != EC_Normal )
405  {
406  sprintf ( msg2, "unknown tag: (%04x,%04x)", g, e );
407  qDebug() << QString ( msg2 );
408  }
409 
410  DcmElement *elem = newDicomElement ( tag );
411 
412  if ( elem == NULL )
413  {
414  sprintf ( msg2, "cannot create element for tag: (%04x,%04x)", g, e );
415  qDebug() << QString ( msg2 );
416  }
417 
418  if ( valStr.length() > 0 )
419  {
420  if ( elem->putString ( valStr.c_str() ).bad() )
421  {
422  sprintf ( msg2, "cannot put tag value: (%04x,%04x)=\"", g, e );
423  msg = msg2;
424  msg += valStr;
425  msg += "\"";
426  qDebug() << QString ( msg.c_str() );
427  }
428  }
429 
430  if ( overrideKeys == NULL )
431  overrideKeys = new DcmDataset;
432 
433  if ( overrideKeys->insert ( elem, OFTrue ).bad() )
434  {
435  sprintf ( msg2, "cannot insert tag: (%04x,%04x)", g, e );
436  qDebug() << QString ( msg2 );
437  }
438 }

440 OFCondition QtDcmMoveScu::addPresentationContext ( T_ASC_Parameters *params, T_ASC_PresentationContextID pid, const char* abstractSyntax, E_TransferSyntax preferredTransferSyntax )
441 {
442  const char* transferSyntaxes[] = { NULL, NULL, NULL };
443  int numTransferSyntaxes = 0;
444 
445  switch ( preferredTransferSyntax )
446  {
447 
448  case EXS_LittleEndianImplicit:
449  /* we only support Little Endian Implicit */
450  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
451  numTransferSyntaxes = 1;
452  break;
453 
454  case EXS_LittleEndianExplicit:
455  /* we prefer Little Endian Explicit */
456  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
457  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
458  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
459  numTransferSyntaxes = 3;
460  break;
461 
462  case EXS_BigEndianExplicit:
463  /* we prefer Big Endian Explicit */
464  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
465  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
466  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
467  numTransferSyntaxes = 3;
468  break;
469 
470  default:
471  /* We prefer explicit transfer syntaxes.
472  * If we are running on a Little Endian machine we prefer
473  * LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax to BigEndianTransferSyntax.
474  */
475 
476  if ( gLocalByteOrder == EBO_LittleEndian ) /* defined in dcxfer.h */
477  {
478  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
479  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
480  }
481  else
482  {
483  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
484  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
485  }
486 
487  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
488 
489  numTransferSyntaxes = 3;
490  break;
491  }
492 
493  return ASC_addPresentationContext (
494 
495  params, pid, abstractSyntax,
496  transferSyntaxes, numTransferSyntaxes );
497 }

499 OFCondition QtDcmMoveScu::acceptSubAssoc ( T_ASC_Network * aNet, T_ASC_Association ** assoc )
500 {
501  const char* knownAbstractSyntaxes[] =
502  {
503  UID_VerificationSOPClass
504  };
505  const char* transferSyntaxes[] = { NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL };
506  int numTransferSyntaxes;
507 
508  OFCondition cond = ASC_receiveAssociation ( aNet, assoc, ASC_DEFAULTMAXPDU );
509 
510  if ( cond.good() )
511  {
512  switch ( EXS_Unknown )
513  {
514 
515  case EXS_LittleEndianImplicit:
516  /* we only support Little Endian Implicit */
517  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
518  numTransferSyntaxes = 1;
519  break;
520 
521  case EXS_LittleEndianExplicit:
522  /* we prefer Little Endian Explicit */
523  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
524  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
525  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
526  numTransferSyntaxes = 3;
527  break;
528 
529  case EXS_BigEndianExplicit:
530  /* we prefer Big Endian Explicit */
531  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
532  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
533  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
534  numTransferSyntaxes = 3;
535  break;
536 
537  case EXS_JPEGProcess14SV1TransferSyntax:
538  /* we prefer JPEGLossless:Hierarchical-1stOrderPrediction (default lossless) */
539  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_JPEGProcess14SV1TransferSyntax;
540  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
541  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
542  transferSyntaxes[3] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
543  numTransferSyntaxes = 4;
544  break;
545 
546  case EXS_JPEGProcess1TransferSyntax:
547  /* we prefer JPEGBaseline (default lossy for 8 bit images) */
548  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_JPEGProcess1TransferSyntax;
549  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
550  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
551  transferSyntaxes[3] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
552  numTransferSyntaxes = 4;
553  break;
554 
555  case EXS_JPEGProcess2_4TransferSyntax:
556  /* we prefer JPEGExtended (default lossy for 12 bit images) */
557  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_JPEGProcess2_4TransferSyntax;
558  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
559  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
560  transferSyntaxes[3] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
561  numTransferSyntaxes = 4;
562  break;
563 
564  case EXS_JPEG2000LosslessOnly:
565  /* we prefer JPEG2000 Lossless */
566  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_JPEG2000LosslessOnlyTransferSyntax;
567  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
568  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
569  transferSyntaxes[3] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
570  numTransferSyntaxes = 4;
571  break;
572 
573  case EXS_JPEG2000:
574  /* we prefer JPEG2000 Lossy */
575  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_JPEG2000TransferSyntax;
576  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
577  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
578  transferSyntaxes[3] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
579  numTransferSyntaxes = 4;
580  break;
581 
582  case EXS_JPEGLSLossless:
583  /* we prefer JPEG-LS Lossless */
584  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_JPEGLSLosslessTransferSyntax;
585  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
586  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
587  transferSyntaxes[3] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
588  numTransferSyntaxes = 4;
589  break;
590 
591  case EXS_JPEGLSLossy:
592  /* we prefer JPEG-LS Lossy */
593  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_JPEGLSLossyTransferSyntax;
594  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
595  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
596  transferSyntaxes[3] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
597  numTransferSyntaxes = 4;
598  break;
599 
600  case EXS_MPEG2MainProfileAtMainLevel:
601  /* we prefer MPEG2 MP@ML */
602  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_MPEG2MainProfileAtMainLevelTransferSyntax;
603  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
604  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
605  transferSyntaxes[3] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
606  numTransferSyntaxes = 4;
607  break;
608 
609  case EXS_RLELossless:
610  /* we prefer RLE Lossless */
611  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_RLELosslessTransferSyntax;
612  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
613  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
614  transferSyntaxes[3] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
615  numTransferSyntaxes = 4;
616  break;
617 #ifdef WITH_ZLIB
618 
619  case EXS_DeflatedLittleEndianExplicit:
620  /* we prefer Deflated Explicit VR Little Endian */
621  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_DeflatedExplicitVRLittleEndianTransferSyntax;
622  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
623  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
624  transferSyntaxes[3] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
625  numTransferSyntaxes = 4;
626  break;
627 #endif
628 
629  default:
630 
631  if ( OFFalse )
632  {
633  /* we accept all supported transfer syntaxes
634  * (similar to "AnyTransferSyntax" in "storescp.cfg")
635  */
636  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_JPEG2000TransferSyntax;
637  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_JPEG2000LosslessOnlyTransferSyntax;
638  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_JPEGProcess2_4TransferSyntax;
639  transferSyntaxes[3] = UID_JPEGProcess1TransferSyntax;
640  transferSyntaxes[4] = UID_JPEGProcess14SV1TransferSyntax;
641  transferSyntaxes[5] = UID_JPEGLSLossyTransferSyntax;
642  transferSyntaxes[6] = UID_JPEGLSLosslessTransferSyntax;
643  transferSyntaxes[7] = UID_RLELosslessTransferSyntax;
644  transferSyntaxes[8] = UID_MPEG2MainProfileAtMainLevelTransferSyntax;
645  transferSyntaxes[9] = UID_DeflatedExplicitVRLittleEndianTransferSyntax;
646 
647  if ( gLocalByteOrder == EBO_LittleEndian )
648  {
649  transferSyntaxes[10] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
650  transferSyntaxes[11] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
651  }
652  else
653  {
654  transferSyntaxes[10] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
655  transferSyntaxes[11] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
656  }
657 
658  transferSyntaxes[12] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
659 
660  numTransferSyntaxes = 13;
661  }
662  else
663  {
664  /* We prefer explicit transfer syntaxes.
665  * If we are running on a Little Endian machine we prefer
666  * LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax to BigEndianTransferSyntax.
667  */
668  if ( gLocalByteOrder == EBO_LittleEndian ) /* defined in dcxfer.h */
669  {
670  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
671  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
672  }
673  else
674  {
675  transferSyntaxes[0] = UID_BigEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
676  transferSyntaxes[1] = UID_LittleEndianExplicitTransferSyntax;
677  }
678 
679  transferSyntaxes[2] = UID_LittleEndianImplicitTransferSyntax;
680 
681  numTransferSyntaxes = 3;
682  }
683 
684  break;
685 
686  }
687 
688  /* accept the Verification SOP Class if presented */
689  cond = ASC_acceptContextsWithPreferredTransferSyntaxes (
690  ( *assoc )->params,
691  knownAbstractSyntaxes, DIM_OF ( knownAbstractSyntaxes ),
692  transferSyntaxes, numTransferSyntaxes );
693 
694  if ( cond.good() )
695  {
696  /* the array of Storage SOP Class UIDs comes from dcuid.h */
697  cond = ASC_acceptContextsWithPreferredTransferSyntaxes (
698  ( *assoc )->params,
699  dcmAllStorageSOPClassUIDs, numberOfAllDcmStorageSOPClassUIDs,
700  transferSyntaxes, numTransferSyntaxes );
701  }
702  }
703 
704  if ( cond.good() ) cond = ASC_acknowledgeAssociation ( *assoc );
705 
706  if ( cond.bad() )
707  {
708  ASC_dropAssociation ( *assoc );
709  ASC_destroyAssociation ( assoc );
710  }
711 
712  return cond;
713 }

727 OFCondition QtDcmMoveScu::storeSCP ( T_ASC_Association *assoc, T_DIMSE_Message *msg, T_ASC_PresentationContextID presID, void* subOpCallbackData )
728 {
729  QtDcmMoveScu * self = ( QtDcmMoveScu* ) subOpCallbackData;
730 
731  OFCondition cond = EC_Normal;
732  T_DIMSE_C_StoreRQ *req;
733  char imageFile[2048];
734 
735  req = &msg->msg.CStoreRQ;
736 
737  if ( OFFalse )
738  {
739 #ifdef _WIN32
740  tmpnam ( imageFile );
741 #else
742  strcpy ( imageFile, NULL_DEVICE_NAME );
743 #endif
744  }
745  else
746  {
747  sprintf ( imageFile, "%s.%s",
748  dcmSOPClassUIDToModality ( req->AffectedSOPClassUID ),
749  req->AffectedSOPInstanceUID );
750  }
751 
752  self->assoc = assoc;
753 
754  self->imageFile = imageFile;

765  }
766 
767  DcmDataset *dset = dcmff.getDataset();
768 
769  if ( OFFalse )
770  {
771  cond = DIMSE_storeProvider ( assoc, presID, req, imageFile, OFFalse,
772  NULL, storeSCPCallback, ( void * ) subOpCallbackData, DIMSE_BLOCKING, 0 );
773  }
774  else
775  {
776  cond = DIMSE_storeProvider ( assoc, presID, req, ( char * ) NULL, OFFalse,
777  &dset, storeSCPCallback, ( void * ) subOpCallbackData, DIMSE_BLOCKING, 0 );
778  }
779 
780  return cond;
781 }

783 void QtDcmMoveScu::storeSCPCallback ( void *callbackData, T_DIMSE_StoreProgress *progress, T_DIMSE_C_StoreRQ *req, char *imageFile, DcmDataset **imageDataSet, T_DIMSE_C_StoreRSP *rsp, DcmDataset **statusDetail )
784 {
785  QtDcmMoveScu* self = ( QtDcmMoveScu* ) callbackData;
786 
787  DIC_UI sopClass;
788  DIC_UI sopInstance;
789 
790  if ( progress->state == DIMSE_StoreEnd )
791  {
792  *statusDetail = NULL;
793 
794  if ( ( imageDataSet != NULL ) && ( *imageDataSet != NULL ) && !self->bitPreserving && !self->ignore )
795  {
796  /* create full path name for the output file */
797  OFString ofname;
798  OFStandard::combineDirAndFilename ( ofname, self->outputDirectory, self->imageFile, OFTrue /* allowEmptyDirName */ );
799 
800  E_TransferSyntax xfer = self->writeTransferSyntax;
801 
802  if ( xfer == EXS_Unknown ) xfer = ( *imageDataSet )->getOriginalXfer();
803 
804  OFCondition cond = self->file->saveFile ( ofname.c_str(), xfer, self->sequenceType, self->groupLength,
805  self->paddingType, OFstatic_cast ( Uint32, self->filepad ), OFstatic_cast ( Uint32, self->itempad ),
806  ( self->useMetaheader ) ? EWM_fileformat : EWM_dataset );
807 
808  if ( QFile ( ofname.c_str() ).exists() )
809  emit self->previewSlice ( QString ( ofname.c_str() ) );
810 
811  if ( ( rsp->DimseStatus == STATUS_Success ) && !self->ignore )
812  {
813  /* which SOP class and SOP instance ? */
814  if ( !DU_findSOPClassAndInstanceInDataSet ( *imageDataSet, sopClass, sopInstance, self->correctUIDPadding ) )
815  {
816  rsp->DimseStatus = STATUS_STORE_Error_CannotUnderstand;
817  }
818  else if ( strcmp ( sopClass, req->AffectedSOPClassUID ) != 0 )
819  {
820  rsp->DimseStatus = STATUS_STORE_Error_DataSetDoesNotMatchSOPClass;
821  }
822  else if ( strcmp ( sopInstance, req->AffectedSOPInstanceUID ) != 0 )
823  {
824  rsp->DimseStatus = STATUS_STORE_Error_DataSetDoesNotMatchSOPClass;
825  }
826  }
827  }
828  }
829 
830  return;
831 }

833 OFCondition QtDcmMoveScu::subOpSCP ( T_ASC_Association **subAssoc, void * subOpCallbackData )
834 {
835  T_DIMSE_Message msg;
836  T_ASC_PresentationContextID presID;
837 
838  if ( !ASC_dataWaiting ( *subAssoc, 0 ) ) /* just in case */
839  return DIMSE_NODATAAVAILABLE;
840 
841  OFCondition cond = DIMSE_receiveCommand ( *subAssoc, DIMSE_BLOCKING, 0, &presID, &msg, NULL );
842 
843  if ( cond == EC_Normal )
844  {
845  switch ( msg.CommandField )
846  {
847 
848  case DIMSE_C_STORE_RQ:
849  cond = storeSCP ( *subAssoc, &msg, presID, subOpCallbackData );
850  break;
851 
852  case DIMSE_C_ECHO_RQ:
853  cond = echoSCP ( *subAssoc, &msg, presID );
854  break;
855 
856  default:
857  cond = DIMSE_BADCOMMANDTYPE;
858  break;
859  }
860  }
861 
862  /* clean up on association termination */
863  if ( cond == DUL_PEERREQUESTEDRELEASE )
864  {
865  cond = ASC_acknowledgeRelease ( *subAssoc );
866  ASC_dropSCPAssociation ( *subAssoc );
867  ASC_destroyAssociation ( subAssoc );
868  return cond;
869  }
870  else if ( cond == DUL_PEERABORTEDASSOCIATION )
871  {
872  }
873  else if ( cond != EC_Normal )
874  {
875  OFString temp_str;
876  qDebug() << "DIMSE failure (aborting sub-association): " << DimseCondition::dump ( temp_str, cond ).c_str();
877  /* some kind of error so abort the association */
878  cond = ASC_abortAssociation ( *subAssoc );
879  }
880 
881  if ( cond != EC_Normal )
882  {
883  ASC_dropAssociation ( *subAssoc );
884  ASC_destroyAssociation ( subAssoc );
885  }
886 
887  return cond;
888 }

890 void QtDcmMoveScu::subOpCallback ( void * caller, T_ASC_Network *aNet, T_ASC_Association **subAssoc )
891 {
892  if ( !caller )
893  return;
894 
895  QtDcmMoveScu * self = ( QtDcmMoveScu* ) caller;
896 
897 // if ( self->getMode() == QtDcmMoveScu::IMPORT )
898  if ( self->slicesCount )
899  emit self->updateProgress ( self->progressTotal + ( int ) ( ( ( float ) ( self->step * ( self->progressSerie ) / self->slicesCount ) ) ) );
900 
901  if ( aNet == NULL ) return; /* help no net ! */
902 
903  if ( *subAssoc == NULL )
904  {
905  /* negotiate association */
906  acceptSubAssoc ( aNet, subAssoc );
907  }
908  else
909  {
910  /* be a service class provider */
911  subOpSCP ( subAssoc, caller );
912  }
913 
914  self->progressSerie ++;
915 }

917 void QtDcmMoveScu::moveCallback ( void *caller, T_DIMSE_C_MoveRQ * req, int responseCount, T_DIMSE_C_MoveRSP * rsp )
918 {
919  if ( !caller )
920  return;
921 
922  QtDcmMoveScu * self = ( QtDcmMoveScu* ) caller;
923 
924  if ( responseCount == 1 )
925  self->progressSerie = 0;
926 
927  self->slicesCount = rsp->NumberOfRemainingSubOperations + rsp->NumberOfFailedSubOperations + rsp->NumberOfWarningSubOperations + rsp->NumberOfCompletedSubOperations;
928 
929  OFCondition cond = EC_Normal;
930 
931  OFString temp_str;
932 
933  DIMSE_dumpMessage ( temp_str, *rsp, DIMSE_INCOMING );
934 
935  qDebug() << "Move Response " << responseCount << ":";
936 
937  qDebug() << QString ( temp_str.c_str() );
938 }

940 void QtDcmMoveScu::substituteOverrideKeys ( DcmDataset *dset )
941 {
942  if ( overrideKeys == NULL )
943  {
944  return; /* nothing to do */
945  }
946 
947  /* copy the override keys */
948  DcmDataset keys ( *overrideKeys );
949 
950  /* put the override keys into dset replacing existing tags */
951  unsigned long elemCount = keys.card();
952 
953  for ( unsigned long i = 0; i < elemCount; i++ )
954  {
955  DcmElement *elem = keys.remove ( ( unsigned long ) 0 );
956 
957  dset->insert ( elem, OFTrue );
958  }
959 }

961 OFCondition QtDcmMoveScu::moveSCU ( T_ASC_Association * assoc, const char *fname )
962 {
963  T_DIMSE_C_MoveRQ req;
964  T_DIMSE_C_MoveRSP rsp;
965  DIC_US msgId = assoc->nextMsgID++;
966  DcmDataset *rspIds = NULL;
967  const char *sopClass;
968  DcmDataset *statusDetail = NULL;
969 
970  QuerySyntax querySyntax[3] =
971  {
972  { UID_FINDPatientRootQueryRetrieveInformationModel,
973  UID_MOVEPatientRootQueryRetrieveInformationModel },
974  { UID_FINDStudyRootQueryRetrieveInformationModel,
975  UID_MOVEStudyRootQueryRetrieveInformationModel },
976  { UID_RETIRED_FINDPatientStudyOnlyQueryRetrieveInformationModel,
977  UID_RETIRED_MOVEPatientStudyOnlyQueryRetrieveInformationModel }
978  };
979 
980 
981  DcmFileFormat file;
982 
983  if ( fname != NULL )
984  {
985  if ( file.loadFile ( fname ).bad() )
986  {
987  qDebug() << "bad DICOM file: " << QString ( fname );
988  return DIMSE_BADDATA;
989  }
990  }
991 
992  /* replace specific keys by those in overrideKeys */
993  substituteOverrideKeys ( file.getDataset() );
994 
995  sopClass = querySyntax[queryModel].moveSyntax;
996 
997  /* which presentation context should be used */
998  presId = ASC_findAcceptedPresentationContextID ( assoc, sopClass );
999 
1000  if ( presId == 0 ) return DIMSE_NOVALIDPRESENTATIONCONTEXTID;
1001 
1002  req.MessageID = msgId;
1003 
1004  strcpy ( req.AffectedSOPClassUID, sopClass );
1005 
1006  req.Priority = DIMSE_PRIORITY_MEDIUM;
1007 
1008  req.DataSetType = DIMSE_DATASET_PRESENT;
1009 
1010  if ( moveDestination == NULL )
1011  {
1012  /* set the destination to be me */
1013  ASC_getAPTitles ( assoc->params, req.MoveDestination,
1014  NULL, NULL );
1015  }
1016  else
1017  {
1018  strcpy ( req.MoveDestination, moveDestination );
1019  }
1020 
1021  OFCondition cond;
1022 
1023  if ( useStoreSCP )
1024  cond = DIMSE_moveUser ( assoc, presId, &req, file.getDataset(), moveCallback, ( void* ) this, blockMode, dimseTimeout, net, subOpCallback, ( void* ) this, &rsp, &statusDetail, &rspIds, ignorePendingDatasets );
1025  else
1026  cond = DIMSE_moveUser ( assoc, presId, &req, file.getDataset(), moveCallback, ( void* ) this, blockMode, dimseTimeout, net, NULL, ( void* ) this, &rsp, &statusDetail, &rspIds, ignorePendingDatasets );
1027 
1028  if ( rspIds != NULL ) delete rspIds;
1029 
1030  return cond;
1031 }
